<div type="translation" source="bib:Hultzsch1890_01">

<p>Prosperity!</p>

<p>(<hi rend="italic">Verse</hi> 1.) She, who, full of loveliness, softness, grace and cleanliness, seemed to be the master-piece of the first creator, whose skill had attained perfection at last, after he had created thousands of good-looking women;—</p>

<p>(2.) She, who was charming through genuine sweetness, who was adorned with grace, coquetry and feeling, who, like the art of attraction, • • • • • </p>

